How to Get Started
Step 1: Register the App
Navigate to your Organization Settings > Developer Settings > GitHub Apps.

Click New GitHub App.

Name: Follow our naming convention: [TeamName]-[Purpose]-Bot.

Homepage URL: Link to your team's Confluence space or the repo documentation.

Webhooks: If you only need to call the API (CLI/Scripts), you can uncheck "Active" for webhooks.

Step 2: Configure Permissions
Only select the minimum permissions required.

Example (CI/CD): Repository permissions > Contents: Read; Metadata: Read.

Example (Bot): Repository permissions > Issues: Read & Write; Pull Requests: Read & Write.

Step 3: Install & Authenticate
Install the App: In the app settings, go to Install App and install it on the specific repositories it needs to access.

Generate Private Key: Under the app settings, scroll to "Private keys" and click Generate a private key. Download the .pem fileâ€”this is your "master key" and should be stored securely (e.g., as a secret in GitHub Actions or your vault).

